--- POST-FIX (densify source_snapshot -- insufficient) ---

Fix applied: source_snapshot in densify_edges(). This addressed a real
mutation-chain issue but was NOT the root cause of the 65.9% area loss.
Densify inserts 0 vertices into panel 8 on real data. The self-intersection
is identical before and after densify.

--- REAL ROOT CAUSE (solver displacement) ---

Running with real DSM + LOG_LEVEL=DEBUG revealed:

  panel 8 invalid after solver: Self-intersection[1.09145448364827 2.60565368007058]

The self-intersection occurs AFTER the solver, BEFORE densify. Densify is innocent.

Solver diagnostic for panel 8 vertex [3] (valence-4 hip apex, panels [1,2,7,8]):
  Pre-solver:  x=49.622714 y=49.837777 z=110.451983
  Post-solver: x=48.289369 y=66.517036 z=110.899241
  Displacement: 16.73 m (!)

Why: The 4 plane normals have near-zero Y components (all ±0.05):
  Panel 1: normal=(-0.563, -0.056, 0.824)
  Panel 2: normal=(0.563,  0.054, 0.824)
  Panel 7: normal=(0.567,  0.046, 0.822)
  Panel 8: normal=(-0.560, -0.056, 0.827)

lstsq singular values: [46.49, 27.08, 0.167]
The 0.167 makes Y poorly constrained. lstsq produces y=66.5 (17m from centroid).
Condition number = 280, well below the 1e8 guard -- so no fallback triggered.

Fix: displacement guard in _solve_valence3 and _solve_valence4plus.
After computing the apex, check XY distance from cluster centroid.
If displacement > 5*tol, fall back to XY centroid + per-plane Z.

--- POST-FIX (solver displacement guard) ---

snap_polygons on fb7e705c with real DSM: SUCCEEDED, all 12 panels survive.
Displacement guard triggered on 2 clusters:
  cluster_id=31 panels=[1,2,7,8] disp=17.0m > max=5.0m -> centroid fallback
  cluster_id=10 panels=[2,4,7]   disp=125.0m > max=5.0m -> centroid fallback
